			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Augment Suggestions<a name="34023"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 11 04 7:01 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Having both the 125 point poison based DD proc on one weapon, and the 50 point life tap on my other, I would say dont waste the points on the life tap proc. Even in main hand, the life tap proc dont go off near as much, and unless you are a class that has a chance for crit heals, the procs are not going to be worth that much to you, as the minial amount of procs you get will not equal that much regenerated hps to you.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
It really depends on why you are selecting a particular  augment to begin with.  In general people select a dd aug to bolster their melee dps.  They pick a life tap aug to bolster their melee dps while at the same time bolstering their own intermediate healing.
<br />

<br />
I went the intermediate healing route using the 50 point life tap.  I like it.  I like it enough that I plan to upgrade it to the 75 point one sometime in the future.  It goes off quite a bit for me.  And I even get critical heals off it, which is a plus.  There have been plenty of times where the life tap has augmented incidental dmg from pulling, along with song and spell regen allowing me to be full health without the need for additional healing, which is the exact reason I chose it.
<br />

<br />
There are additional augs that aren't mentioned, like Guard and Spell Guard, just to name two off the top of my head.  Ask around on input, study the augs available, then decide which augment best suits your situation, for in the end it is your choice, and one you will have to life with.
<br />

<br />
Polara Magami
<br />
64 Melodic Disciple</span></td>
