				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Augment Suggestions<a name="34547"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 13 04 10:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you pull most of the time (as most bards do) you WILL regularly get smacked and lifetaps are really handy.  Also as a bard you will occasionally find yourself on rampage list no matter how careful you are, especially as rampage lists seem to have gone a bit beserk recently.   Mob AE's will hit you and lifetaps are great for this. If you get dotted, good lifetaps will significantly reduce the damage you are taking. Basically as an active bard you WILL take damage when you are not tanking.  
<br />

<br />
Personally I'm going lifetap all the way, I have AHB (100pt unresistible lifetap), and am saving up for 75pt lifetap to add to that, and have 50pt in my epic.  In addition I now have WA5 and I'm completely convinced from personal experience that this is an awesome strategy for weapon augments.  
<br />

<br />
In those situations where you are takin dmg, then each lifetap that goes off is the same as having extra hitpoints.   I have the 50pt in my epic, if that goes off 3 times in a fight thats an effective extra 150 hit pts.  How much would you pay to augment your epic with 150 hit points?
<br />

<br />
Look at it another way, mainhand weaps proc roughly 2x per minute and with WA5 thats roughly 3 times a minute.  Thats a regen of ~300hps/minute or ~30pts/tick with AHB.  A 50pt proc in offhand will probably work out as equivalent to regen 5, and thats before I have even bought the 75pt aug.  
<br />

<br />
Lifetaps own</span></td>
