				<td colspan="2"><span>I can't believe you're excited about a 35 pt regen!  I mean, you have about the purest lifetap setup available (including WA5!), and yet, it's still only adding 35 hps/tick.   
<br />

<br />
At your level of play, mobs are hitting you for 1000 routinely.  And, I'm sure you almost always have either a shammy or a cleric in your group.  At least from my experience, as the puller, any healer worth anything is gonna gonna slap a HoT on me as soon as I drop 20%.  Most the time, even the cheapest heal over time is mostly wasted as overkill.
<br />

<br />
Sure... if I had that extra 35 hps/tick, I'd regen hps back a tad faster, but that totallly assumes that the healers forget to heal me or that my shammy is low on mana (shhawww.... right!).  No way are people gonna wait around for me to regen back up so that I can pull again. 
<br />

<br />
If yer looking at efficiency and effective use of yer points, lifetaps are not the way to go.  If you do it cause it's fun, knock yerself out.  I say, kill the mob faster and get a low-cost heal over time.
<br />

<br />
Wyndaria.
