				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Augment Suggestions<a name="34785"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 15 04 10:16 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a Lunar Fungus Tunic from VT.  It is like a Fungi with way better stats.  I also have a lot of regen items, when I put em all on I can can get a LOT of regen.  When I raid however, I slap on Vindi BP for extra AC, and swap out other gear as well.  Regen is fine for exp groups or soloing where there is no healer.   Worn regen that is.  I dont consider a Lifetap proc to be regen of any kind, the hp you get from it is doesnt really matter.
<br />
Regen is nice, but it isnt healing.  With the best regen songs, buffs, and gear, in the time in takes to REGEN 2k hp, you should have killed any mob a normal exp group can kill.
<br />
If you are a raiding bard, and are getting hit for that much, unless you are the MT there is probably something wrong.  If the mob is AEIng that much, then your raid probably has an AE heal rot going.  Again, if you are relying on your regen to survive, you have some problems with aggro or healers.
<br />
No matter what you are fighting, the main focus of the group or raid is to KILL THE MOB.  Usually as fast as possible, unless its an OT mob that needs to stay alive for whatever reason.  Our song selection normally reflects this need to kill fast.  Our gear selection should too.  That inlcudes augs.  If you think a 75 lifetap proc or regen III aug helps you kill the mobs faster then a Veng V or 150DD proc, then more power to ya.
<br />

<br />
You might be right about the nothing hitting for 6k Mel.  But lots of things hit for 1-2k and quad....  You normally dont fight those in groups however.
<br />
If you are slapping a lifetap proc on a weapon for the HEALING, then you are living waaaay to close to the edge ;o)
<br />
